    <abstract>
      <t>&lt;p&gt;eBPF (which is no longer an acronym for anything), also commonly referred to as BPF, is a technology with origins in the Linux kernel that can run untrusted programs in a privileged context such as an operating system kernel.  This document specifies the BPF instruction set architecture (ISA).&lt;/p&gt;</t>
